      <chapter eId="chp_720">
        <num>720</num>
        <heading>DIGITAL SIGNATURES</heading>
        <section eId="sec_720-010">
          <num>720.010</num>
          <heading>Definitions.</heading>
          <content>
            <p>As
used in this chapter, unless the context otherwise requires, the words and
terms defined inNRS 720.020to720.130, inclusive, have the meanings
ascribed to them in those sections.</p>
          </content>
          <authorialNote marker="history">
            <p>ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ (Added to NRS by1999,
1953; A2001,
2722)</p>
          </authorialNote>
        </section>
        <section eId="sec_720-020">
          <num>720.020</num>
          <heading>ï¿½Asymmetric cryptosystemï¿½ defined.</heading>
          <content>
            <p>ï¿½Asymmetric
cryptosystemï¿½ means an algorithm or series of algorithms that provide a secure
key pair.</p>
          </content>
          <authorialNote marker="history">
            <p>ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ (Added to NRS by1999,
1953)</p>
          </authorialNote>
        </section>
        <section eId="sec_720-030">
          <num>720.030</num>
          <heading>ï¿½Certificateï¿½ defined.</heading>
          <subsection eId="720-030__subsec_1">
            <num>1.</num>
            <content>
              <p>Identifies the certification authority
using it;
ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½</p>
            </content>
          </subsection>
          <subsection eId="720-030__subsec_2">
            <num>2.</num>
            <content>
              <p>Identifies a subscriber;
ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½</p>
            </content>
          </subsection>
          <subsection eId="720-030__subsec_3">
            <num>3.</num>
            <content>
              <p>Sets forth the public key of the
subscriber; and
ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½</p>
            </content>
          </subsection>
          <subsection eId="720-030__subsec_4">
            <num>4.</num>
            <content>
              <p>Is digitally signed by the
certification authority issuing it.</p>
            </content>
          </subsection>
          <authorialNote marker="history">
            <p>ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ (Added to NRS by1999,
1953)</p>
          </authorialNote>
        </section>
        <section eId="sec_720-040">
          <num>720.040</num>
          <heading>ï¿½Certification authorityï¿½ defined.</heading>
          <content>
            <p>ï¿½Certification
authorityï¿½ means a person who issues a certificate.</p>
          </content>
          <authorialNote marker="history">
            <p>ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ (Added to NRS by1999,
1953)</p>
          </authorialNote>
        </section>
        <section eId="sec_720-050">
          <num>720.050</num>
          <heading>ï¿½Correspondï¿½ defined.</heading>
          <content>
            <p>ï¿½Correspondï¿½
means, with reference to keys, belonging to the same key pair.</p>
          </content>
          <authorialNote marker="history">
            <p>ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ (Added to NRS by1999,
1953)</p>
          </authorialNote>
        </section>
        <section eId="sec_720-060">
          <num>720.060</num>
          <heading>ï¿½Digital signatureï¿½ defined.</heading>
          <content>
            <p>ï¿½Digital
signatureï¿½ means an electronic signature that transforms a message by using an
asymmetric cryptosystem. As used in this section, ï¿½electronic signatureï¿½ has
the meaning ascribed to it inNRS 719.100.</p>
          </content>
          <authorialNote marker="history">
            <p>ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ (Added to NRS by1999,
1953; A2001,
2722)</p>
          </authorialNote>
        </section>
        <section eId="sec_720-070">
          <num>720.070</num>
          <heading>ï¿½Hold a private keyï¿½ defined.</heading>
          <content>
            <p>ï¿½Hold
a private keyï¿½ means to be authorized to use a private key.</p>
          </content>
          <authorialNote marker="history">
            <p>ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ (Added to NRS by1999,
1954)</p>
          </authorialNote>
        </section>
        <section eId="sec_720-080">
          <num>720.080</num>
          <heading>ï¿½Key pairï¿½ defined.</heading>
          <content>
            <p>ï¿½Key
pairï¿½ means a private key and its corresponding public key in an asymmetric
cryptosystem, which may be used in such a manner that the public key can verify
a digital signature created by the private key.</p>
          </content>
          <authorialNote marker="history">
            <p>ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ (Added to NRS by1999,
1954)</p>
          </authorialNote>
        </section>
        <section eId="sec_720-090">
          <num>720.090</num>
          <heading>ï¿½Messageï¿½ defined.</heading>
          <content>
            <p>ï¿½Messageï¿½
means a digital representation of information.</p>
          </content>
          <authorialNote marker="history">
            <p>ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ (Added to NRS by1999,
1954)</p>
          </authorialNote>
        </section>
        <section eId="sec_720-100">
          <num>720.100</num>
          <heading>ï¿½Private keyï¿½ defined.</heading>
          <content>
            <p>ï¿½Private
keyï¿½ means the key of a key pair used to create a digital signature.</p>
          </content>
          <authorialNote marker="history">
            <p>ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ (Added to NRS by1999,
1954)</p>
          </authorialNote>
        </section>
        <section eId="sec_720-110">
          <num>720.110</num>
          <heading>ï¿½Public keyï¿½ defined.</heading>
          <content>
            <p>ï¿½Public
keyï¿½ means the key of a key pair used to verify a digital signature.</p>
          </content>
          <authorialNote marker="history">
            <p>ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ (Added to NRS by1999,
1954)</p>
          </authorialNote>
        </section>
        <section eId="sec_720-115">
          <num>720.115</num>
          <heading>ï¿½Recordï¿½ defined.</heading>
          <content>
            <p>ï¿½Recordï¿½
has the meaning ascribed to it inNRS
719.150.</p>
          </content>
          <authorialNote marker="history">
            <p>ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ (Added to NRS by2001,
2721)</p>
          </authorialNote>
        </section>
        <section eId="sec_720-120">
          <num>720.120</num>
          <heading>ï¿½Subscriberï¿½ defined.</heading>
          <subsection eId="720-120__subsec_1">
            <num>1.</num>
            <content>
              <p>Is identified as such in a certificate;
ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½</p>
            </content>
          </subsection>
          <subsection eId="720-120__subsec_2">
            <num>2.</num>
            <content>
              <p>Accepts the certificate; and
ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½</p>
            </content>
          </subsection>
          <subsection eId="720-120__subsec_3">
            <num>3.</num>
            <content>
              <p>Holds the private key that corresponds
to the public key set forth in the certificate.</p>
            </content>
          </subsection>
          <authorialNote marker="history">
            <p>ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ (Added to NRS by1999,
1954)</p>
          </authorialNote>
        </section>
        <section eId="sec_720-130">
          <num>720.130</num>
          <heading>ï¿½Verify a digital signatureï¿½ defined.</heading>
          <subsection eId="720-130__subsec_1">
            <num>1.</num>
            <content>
              <p>The digital signature was created by
the private key corresponding to the public key; and
ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½</p>
            </content>
          </subsection>
          <subsection eId="720-130__subsec_2">
            <num>2.</num>
            <content>
              <p>The message has not been altered since
the digital signature was created.</p>
            </content>
          </subsection>
          <authorialNote marker="history">
            <p>ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ (Added to NRS by1999,
1954)</p>
          </authorialNote>
        </section>
        <section eId="sec_720-140">
          <num>720.140</num>
          <heading>Applicability of chapter.</heading>
          <subsection eId="720-140__subsec_1">
            <num>1.</num>
            <content>
              <p>Except as otherwise provided in this
subsection, the provisions of this chapter apply to any transaction for which a
digital signature is used to sign an electronic record. The provisions of this
chapter do not apply to a digital signature that is used to sign an electronic
health record in accordance withNRS 439.581to439.597, inclusive, and the
regulations adopted pursuant thereto.
ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½</p>
            </content>
          </subsection>
          <subsection eId="720-140__subsec_2">
            <num>2.</num>
            <content>
              <p>As used in this section, ï¿½electronic
recordï¿½ has the meaning ascribed to it inNRS
719.090.</p>
            </content>
          </subsection>
          <authorialNote marker="history">
            <p>ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ (Added to NRS by1999,
1954; A2001,
2722;2011,
1766;2023,
1857)</p>
          </authorialNote>
        </section>
        <section eId="sec_720-150">
          <num>720.150</num>
          <heading>Adoption of regulations by Secretary of State.</heading>
          <subsection eId="720-150__subsec_1">
            <num>1.</num>
            <content>
              <p>The use of a digital signature,
including, without limitation, standards for the commercial use of a digital
signature;
ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½</p>
            </content>
          </subsection>
          <subsection eId="720-150__subsec_2">
            <num>2.</num>
            <content>
              <p>Licensure of a certification authority,
including, without limitation, professional standards that a certification
authority must meet in conducting its business;
ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½</p>
            </content>
          </subsection>
          <subsection eId="720-150__subsec_3">
            <num>3.</num>
            <content>
              <p>The verification of a digital
signature;
ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½</p>
            </content>
          </subsection>
          <subsection eId="720-150__subsec_4">
            <num>4.</num>
            <content>
              <p>The liability that may be incurred by a
subscriber, certification authority or recipient of a message transformed by a
digital signature, including, without limitation, the limitation of such
liability;
ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½</p>
            </content>
          </subsection>
          <subsection eId="720-150__subsec_5">
            <num>5.</num>
            <content>
              <p>The use of a digital signature as an
acknowledgment, as that term is defined inNRS
240.002;
ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½</p>
            </content>
          </subsection>
          <subsection eId="720-150__subsec_6">
            <num>6.</num>
            <content>
              <p>The issuance of injunctions and orders
and the imposition of civil penalties pursuant toNRS 720.190;
ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½</p>
            </content>
          </subsection>
          <subsection eId="720-150__subsec_7">
            <num>7.</num>
            <content>
              <p>The status of a private key as personal
property;
ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½</p>
            </content>
          </subsection>
          <subsection eId="720-150__subsec_8">
            <num>8.</num>
            <content>
              <p>The responsibilities of a subscriber
with respect to the use and handling of a private key;
ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½</p>
            </content>
          </subsection>
          <subsection eId="720-150__subsec_9">
            <num>9.</num>
            <content>
              <p>The confidentiality of information represented
in a message that is transformed by a digital signature; and
ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½</p>
            </content>
          </subsection>
          <subsection eId="720-150__subsec_10">
            <num>10.</num>
            <content>
              <p>Any other aspect of the use or
verification of digital signatures that the Secretary of State determines to be
necessary.</p>
            </content>
          </subsection>
          <authorialNote marker="history">
            <p>ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ (Added to NRS by1999,
1955)</p>
          </authorialNote>
        </section>
        <section eId="sec_720-160">
          <num>720.160</num>
          <heading>Use of digital signature.</heading>
          <subsection eId="720-160__subsec_1">
            <num>1.</num>
            <content>
              <p>Except as otherwise provided in this
section, if each person who will be involved in the submission and acceptance
of a record agrees to the use of a digital signature, the use of a message
which:
ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½</p>
            </content>
            <paragraph eId="720-160__subsec_1__subsec_a">
              <num>(a)</num>
              <content>
                <p>Represents the record; and
ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½</p>
              </content>
            </paragraph>
            <paragraph eId="720-160__subsec_1__subsec_b">
              <num>(b)</num>
              <content>
                <p>Is transformed by a digital signature,
ï¿½constitutes
a sufficient signing of the record.
ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½</p>
              </content>
            </paragraph>
          </subsection>
          <subsection eId="720-160__subsec_2">
            <num>2.</num>
            <content>
              <p>The provisions of this section do not
apply with respect to:
ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½</p>
            </content>
            <paragraph eId="720-160__subsec_2__subsec_a">
              <num>(a)</num>
              <content>
                <p>A record that is required to be signed in the
presence of a third party; or
ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½</p>
              </content>
            </paragraph>
            <paragraph eId="720-160__subsec_2__subsec_b">
              <num>(b)</num>
              <content>
                <p>A record with respect to which the
requirement that the record must be signed is accompanied by an additional
qualifying requirement.</p>
              </content>
            </paragraph>
          </subsection>
          <authorialNote marker="history">
            <p>ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ (Added to NRS by1999,
1954; A2001,
2722)</p>
          </authorialNote>
        </section>
        <section eId="sec_720-180">
          <num>720.180</num>
          <heading>Licensure of certification authorities: Requirement; fee.</heading>
          <subsection eId="720-180__subsec_1">
            <num>1.</num>
            <content>
              <p>A person shall not conduct business as
a certification authority without first obtaining a license as a certification
authority from the Secretary of State.
ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½</p>
            </content>
          </subsection>
          <subsection eId="720-180__subsec_2">
            <num>2.</num>
            <content>
              <p>The Secretary of State may charge a
reasonable fee for such licensure.</p>
            </content>
          </subsection>
          <authorialNote marker="history">
            <p>ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ (Added to NRS by1999,
1955)</p>
          </authorialNote>
        </section>
        <section eId="sec_720-190">
          <num>720.190</num>
          <heading>Enforcement of chapter: Injunctions and other orders; civil
penalty.</heading>
          <subsection eId="720-190__subsec_1">
            <num>1.</num>
            <content>
              <p>Issue injunctions and orders to enforce
the provisions of this chapter and any regulations adopted by the Secretary of
State pursuant thereto.
ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½</p>
            </content>
          </subsection>
          <subsection eId="720-190__subsec_2">
            <num>2.</num>
            <content>
              <p>Impose a civil penalty not to exceed
$10,000 for a willful violation of a provision of this chapter or a regulation
adopted by the Secretary of State pursuant thereto.</p>
            </content>
          </subsection>
          <authorialNote marker="history">
            <p>ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ (Added to NRS by1999,
1955)</p>
          </authorialNote>
        </section>
        <section eId="sec_720-200">
          <num>720.200</num>
          <heading>Unlawful acts; penalty.</heading>
          <subsection eId="720-200__subsec_1">
            <num>1.</num>
            <content>
              <p>It is unlawful for a person to:
ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½</p>
            </content>
            <paragraph eId="720-200__subsec_1__subsec_a">
              <num>(a)</num>
              <content>
                <p>Forge a digital signature; or
ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½</p>
              </content>
            </paragraph>
            <paragraph eId="720-200__subsec_1__subsec_b">
              <num>(b)</num>
              <content>
                <p>Provide false information knowingly to the
Secretary of State with respect to any provision of this chapter or a
regulation adopted pursuant thereto that requires such a person to provide
information to the Secretary of State.
ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½</p>
              </content>
            </paragraph>
          </subsection>
          <subsection eId="720-200__subsec_2">
            <num>2.</num>
            <content>
              <p>A person who violates the provisions of
subsection 1 is guilty of a gross misdemeanor.
ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½</p>
            </content>
          </subsection>
          <subsection eId="720-200__subsec_3">
            <num>3.</num>
            <content>
              <p>As used in this section, ï¿½forge a
digital signatureï¿½ means to create a digital signature that:
ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½</p>
            </content>
            <paragraph eId="720-200__subsec_3__subsec_a">
              <num>(a)</num>
              <content>
                <p>Is not authorized by the person who holds the
private key used to create the digital signature; or
ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½</p>
              </content>
            </paragraph>
            <paragraph eId="720-200__subsec_3__subsec_b">
              <num>(b)</num>
              <content>
                <p>Although verifiable by a public key, the
certificate that contains the public key identifies a subscriber who:
ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½</p>
              </content>
              <subparagraph eId="720-200__subsec_3__subsec_b__subsec_1">
                <num>(1)</num>
                <content>
                  <p>Does not exist; or
ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½</p>
                </content>
              </subparagraph>
              <subparagraph eId="720-200__subsec_3__subsec_b__subsec_2">
                <num>(2)</num>
                <content>
                  <p>Does not hold the private key that
corresponds to the public key contained in the certificate.</p>
                </content>
              </subparagraph>
            </paragraph>
          </subsection>
          <authorialNote marker="history">
            <p>ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ (Added to NRS by1999,
1955)</p>
          </authorialNote>
        </section>
